a 56 year old bronx woman and her 81 year old mother were severely injured early yesterday in a fire that destroyed their third floor apartment the authorities said the fire department said the younger woman margrit widerman a high school teacher and her mother kathe schattner who is known to neighbors as grandma were in critical condition yesterday in the intensive care unit of jacobi medical center both suffered from burns and smoke inhalation the cause of the fire at 2081 cruger avenue in the pelham parkway section was careless smoking according to the fire department neighbors in the six story apartment building were awakened minutes after midnight by exploding windows and flames from the apartment shattered glass littered the sidewalk along brady avenue and black soot stained a wall of the apartment building the fire which was reported at 12 04 am was under control at 12 32 am the rest of the building sustained only minor damage fire officials said

